PRESIDENT John Magufuli has made a minor cabinet reshuffle by appointing Innocent Bashungwa as Minister of Industry and Trade. Mr Bashungwa is replacing Joseph Kakunda whose appointment has been revoked. According to a State House press statement released on Saturday morning, Dr Magufuli appointed Mr Edwin Mhede as Commissioner General of Tanzania Revenue Authority (TRA) to fill the vacuum left by Mr Charles Kichere whose appointment has been revoked. Prior to his appointment, Mhede was Deputy Permanent Secretary of Ministry of Trade and Industry. The former taxman Kichere has been appointed as Njombeâ€™s Regional Administrative Officer (RAS) to replace Erick Shitindi who is retiring from public service.